{"parentUuid":"ce416f1c-88dd-42c0-bb08-45ba64a15d36","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AKd8qbmvKUoEuJRPhRiMDF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Given your situation, a home server won't work well — you're moving countries and family is worldwide, so you need cloud hosting. Here's a clear breakdown of your realistic options:\n\n---\n\n**Option A — Free & Simple (Netlify)**\n- Cost: **Free**\n- You update the site by dragging files into a folder on your computer, then syncing\n- Password protection for the whole site (one shared password for family)\n- Best for: photos, short video clips\n- Limitation: large videos may be slow/expensive to serve; updating requires a little technical comfort\n\n**Option B — Cheap & Full-Featured (~$5–6/month)**\n- A small cloud server (e.g. DigitalOcean or Hetzner)\n- I build you a proper web app with a **browser-based upload panel** — you log in, drag photos/videos in, add captions, organise albums\n- Family gets a separate view-only password\n- Handles large videos well\n- Best all-round for your use case\n\n**Option C — Specialised Photo App (self-hosted)**\n- Install an existing app like **Immich** or **Piwigo** on a server\n- Very powerful (auto-organisation, mobile apps, etc.)\n- More complex to set up and maintain\n\n---\n\n**My recommendation for you: Option B.**\n\nIt's affordable, works from anywhere in the world, survives your move, and I can build it so updating is as easy as using a website. You won't need to touch any code once it's running.\n\nAre you comfortable paying ~$5–6/month for hosting? And do you have a domain name already, or would you need one (usually ~$10–15/year)?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":721,"cache_read_input_tokens":8395,"output_tokens":914,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","c