{"parentUuid":"957c9c2b-ce0a-4ffb-b600-632d0ca9a85f","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017YxoTfXoLB4aMtZJznjMm3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"With **Option B**, your website lives entirely on the cloud server — not on your laptop. So:\n\n- Upgrade your SSD → no problem\n- Get a new laptop → no problem\n- Move to a different country → no problem\n- Use your wife's computer → no problem\n\nAll you need is **a web browser and your password**. You log into your site's admin panel from any device, anywhere in the world, and upload photos/videos just like you would on Google Photos or Facebook.\n\nNothing is tied to your specific computer. The server in the cloud runs 24/7 regardless of what happens to your hardware.\n\nThis is one of the big advantages of going the cloud route given your situation — it's completely hardware-independent and location-independent.\n\nWant to go ahead with that approach? If so, the next steps would be:\n\n1. Sign up for a cloud server (I'll walk you through it — takes about 10 minutes)\n2. Optionally register a domain name (e.g. `smith-family.com`)\n3. I build the website and deploy it for you"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":938,"cache_read_input_tokens":9116,"output_tokens":381,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":938,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaNzR5xoq2dk1u9t9CahU","type":"assistant","uuid":"e5962da9-4407-4637-b6dc-aecc7ec7fd95","timestamp":"2026-04-24T17:28:42.048Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"C:\\Users\\mcopp","sessionId":"84cd6d84-f430-4fc3-b7e7-8e72fa309448","version":"2.1.80","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
